title: S.J. girls: Royster lifts Delran
text:
More coverage: Southeastern Pa. high school sports 
In other Burlington County League action: 
Morgan Morocco scored a goal and had an assist for Holy Cross in a 3-0 win over visiting Northern Burlington. Jenna Merchell and Erica Wallace also scored. 
Hailey Russell scored a hat trick for host Riverside in a 3-0 win over Burlington City. 
Penn-Jersey League. Imani Young scored two goals in Life Center's 4-3 win over host Doane Academy. Kyla Gumbs and Winnie Tyobee also scored. 
Tri-County Diamond. Ashley Krivda netted two goals in a 3-0 victory for visiting Woodstown over Penns Grove. Paige Caldwell also scored. 
Nonleague. Nicole Binkley, Brooke Cover, and JennaRose Scimone each scored goals for Burlington Township in a 3-1 comeback win over host Moorestown Friends. Field Hockey 
Taylor Gresh made seven saves for Overbrook in a 1-0 overtime win over visiting Sterling in a Colonial Conference game. 
Alyssa Cavallaro scored the winning goal thanks to a pass from Serena Pearson. 
Rachel Kane made four saves for Sterling. 
In other Colonial Conference action: 
Jillian Caputo made six saves in Haddon Township's 3-0 win over visiting Paulsboro. Hannah Furey, Julia Haigh, and Tori Howard provided the offense, each scoring a goal. 
Ciara Girouard, Kristina Jakubowski, and Christina Petito each scored a goal for host West Deptford in a 3-0 triumph over Audubon. Girouard also had an assist. 
Jaimie McCormick and Suzie Clark each had a goal and an assist, and host Haddonfield defeated Collingswood, 6-0. Megan Maynes made six saves. Girls' Tennis 
Jessica Errigo, of top- seeded Seneca, rallied to win, 5-7, 6-3, 6-3, at first singles, and the hosts defeated No. 4 Ocean City, 3-2, in the South Jersey Group 3 semifinals. 
S.J. Non-Public A Semis. Caitlin Deffler won both sets by the score of 6-2 at second singles, and No. 1 Bishop Eustace defeated visiting No. 2 St. Rose, 4 1/2 -1 1/2. The third singles match ended in a draw. 
C.J. Group 1 Semifinals. Sarah Bruno of No. 5 Haddon Township won 6-1, 6-1, and the host Hawks defeated No. 9 Metuchen, 4-1. Girls' Volleyball 
Madison Cole tallied 10 kills, four blocks, and Kingsway defeatined host Northern Burlington 2-1, in an Olympic Conference match.
